radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is borderline in size, measuring 6 mm, but is fluid filled, and multiple appendicoliths are seen. There is slight right lower quadrant inflammatory stranding. The lung bases demonstrate no nodule, opacity or pleural effusion. The liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, ureters and small bowel appear unremarkable. The rectum, sigmoid colon and bladder appear unremarkable. The prostate appears normal. Osseous structures appear unremarkable. There is no evidence of bowel obstruction and no abnormal fluid collection to suggest abscess.
